put a hydraulik jack under the bar when the rubber is on and de bolt and nut 
in de place[but not fully thighten yet] pres the bar fermly but not to 
strong against steering house , then put a glueclamp on de bracket and press 
it , , with a small hammer you can put the retainer clip on ,  i hope you 
understand , i don,t know all the right names in englis greetings from 
amsterdam co


